student_answer: there are four major steps involved in protein synthesis the creation of mana the creation of the protein the polishing of the protein and packaging of the protein the first step the creation of mana takes place i the nucleus the nucleus has many extra nitrogenous bases (adenine, cytokine guanine, thymine, and uracil) floating around in the nucleic cytoplasm it uses define (a), cytokine (c), gunning (g), and trail but to make mana first the dna unravels to the section needed to make the specific protein then the tuna reads the dna creating the mana by matching up the a ca go and t(thymine) on the dna with the up go ca and a on the mana respectively.the second step the creation of the protein takes place in the cytoplasm on a ribosome. the rena in the ribosome reads the mana to decide what amino acids to used the mana consists of coons sets of three nitrogenous bases which correspond to a specific amino acid the ribosome creates a long amino acid chain known as a polypeptide chain.the third step the polishing of the protein takes place in the ectoplasmic reticular (er). after the polypeptide chain floats over to the era the er puts the finishing touches on the chain.the fourth step the packaging of the protein takes place in the gold apparatus the gold apparatus packages the protein to get it ready to travel to its location out of the cell then the protein is sent to the part of the body where it's needed
